Not sure about those of you that didn't get it to work. I managed to get mine to work. You'll have to extract all the files into one folder. Open the zipped file called zwt.rar as the others will go from zwt.rar01-08. You'll be able to access the .exe for the utilities as well as the keygen. I do agree with m0nst3rmash about having it just compressed it into one zip, but seeing as it has worked for me, I can't really complain. Thank you MAFIAA!!!

This does work, don't listen to the people that says it doesn't. They probably lack the knowledge to read...

1. To be able to extract the setup-file you have to extract ALL of the rar-files twice otherwise it wont give you a complete file.

2. Install Dameware (next, next, next installation)

3. Start the keygen that is included in the download, choose Dameware NT utilities and press generate. This should create a file called "dwabin.txt" THIS FILE WILL BE CREATED IN THE FOLDER WHERE YOU OPEN THE KEYGEN FROM.

4.Start Dameware, go to Help > About DNTU.

5. Click and drag the "dwabin.txt"-file and drop it over the "About DameWare NT Utilities" window. 

6. You are good to go
